    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - 12/06/1994 and After - SPECIFICATIONS - SYSTEM
        OPERATING TEST
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="test" graphiccount="0">
        <title>SYSTEM OPERATING TEST</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>This test is used to determine if the air conditioning system is properly charged and is functioning
                correctly. The test is performed using a manifold gauge set, 2 thermometers and an electronic leak
                detector.
            </para>
            <para>Run the test under the following conditions:</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Connect Manifold Gauge Set to the A/C system.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Insert a thermometer into the center air conditioning duct. Do not allow thermometer to touch
                        the side of the duct.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Position a thermometer approxi- mately 12 to 24 inches (30 to 60 cm) in front of the vehicle
                        grille to measure ambient temperature of air entering the condenser.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Run the engine at 1800 RPM.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Set the A/C control for maximum cooling, blower switch on high and heater off.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Open both cab doors.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>If the vehicle has radiator shutters, open them.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>If it has a fan drive, engage it. The shutters and fan can be operated with a jumper wire or
                        by disconnecting the solenoid valve, depending on the system.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </svcprocinfo>
